    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 5000i and 9000i - CATERPILLAR C-10, C-12 AND 3406E ENGINES -
        TROUBLESHOOTING - Cruise and PTO Controls
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Cruise and PTO Controls</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to Caterpillar Electronic Troubleshooting Guide to diagnose a cruise system malfunction.</para>
            <para>The EZ-Tech or Pro-Link Electronic Service Tools (EST) can be used to monitor system parameters
                relating to Cruise Control operation. Use the EST to monitor operation of system switches, including the
                Cruise On/Off, Set/Resume, service brake and clutch switch.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Disconnecting (400) from the ECM will cause incremental amounts of Trip Data to be lost. An
                        "Event Recorder Data Lost" code may also be logged. The loss of this data will not affect engine
                        operation, but will affect the accuracy of the data. Ask the owner/operator if they want data
                        recorded before disconnecting.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Cruise On/Off Switch and Circuits</title>
            <table id="t0821610" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Cruise On/Off Switch and Circuits</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.56in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.79in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.90in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.69in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.90in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.24in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect conn. (435) from cruise on/off switch. With switch in the on position
                                    measure resistance between terminals 5 and 6.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Across cruise on/off switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;2 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect conn. (400) from ECM. Measure the resistance between conn. (435),
                                    terminal 6 and ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(435), 97-GC to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 97-GC, or 97-GB between conn. (435) and
                                    ground, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At conn. (400) use test lead to jumper terminal 59 (circuit 97AE) to terminal 5
                                    (circuit 97-G). At connector (435), measure resistance between circuits 97AE and
                                    97-GC.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(435), 97AE to 97-GC.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Cruise on/off switch and circuits to (400) check good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 97AE between connectors (435) and (400),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Cruise Set/Resume Switch and Circuits</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Disconnecting (400) from the ECM will cause incremental amounts of Trip Data to be lost. An
                        "Event Recorder Data Lost" code may also be logged. The loss of this data will not affect engine
                        operation, but will affect the accuracy of the data. Ask the owner/operator if they want data
                        recorded before disconnecting.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t0821611" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Cruise Set/Resume Switch and Circuits</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.55in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.88in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.83in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.74in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.81in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.28in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Remove conn. (436) from cruise set/resume switch. With switch in neutral position,
                                    measure resistance between switch terminal 2 and terminals 1 and 3.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Set/ resume switch, 2 to 1 and 2 to 3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace set/ resume switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With switch in resume position, measure resistance between switch terminals 1 and
                                    2.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Set/resume switch, 1 to 2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;2 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace set/ resume switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With switch in set position, measure resistance between switch terminals 2 and
                                    3.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Set/ resume switch 2 to 3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;2 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace set/ resume switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect conn. (400) from ECM. Measure the resistance between conn. (436)
                                    terminal 2 and ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(436), 97-GB to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 97-GB, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At conn. (400), use test lead to jumper terminal 5 (circuit 97-G) to 44 (circuit
                                    97AA). At conn. (436) measure resistance between circuits 97AA and 97-GB.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(436), 97AA to 97-GB.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 97AA between connectors (436) and (400),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At conn. (400) use test lead to jumper terminal 5 (circuit 97-G) to 35 (circuit
                                    97AB). At conn. (436) measure resistance between circuits 97AB and 97-GB.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(436) 97AB to 97-GB.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>The set/ resume switch and circuits test good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 97AB between connectors (436) and (400),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
